It gauges how well the template can communicate with the related functional monomer. Strong interactions have a high value, while weak species have a low α value. The slope of the calibration curve for OST determined at the CC/AuCD/ePDA-MIP (SMIP
                     ) was 865.81 and that for the CC/AuCD/ePDA-NIP (SNIP
                     ) was 57.408. As a result, the imprinting factor was equivalent to 15.08 and showed that DA monomer and OST interacted strongly.
